GET LOCAL PIZZA

As the nation’s largest community of independent pizzerias, it’s an honor to celebrate National Pizza Day with a retrospective of the past year in pie.

We measured the mozzarella, charted the crusts, and munched the numbers from millions of ’22 orders to see what’s new with everyone’s favorite food and the pizzerias that make it possible.

PREDICTED TRENDS FOR 2023

Roman-Style Pizza

When in Rome (or your local pizzeria), eat as the Romans do! We’re seeing an uptick in Roman-style pies: sauce and toppings right up to the edges of thin crusts.

Fun Fact: This style of pizza is traditionally priced by weight, like deli meat! Learn more from a Roman-style expert on our How You Slice It podcast.

Pickle Pizza

Here’s the dill: Pickle pizza went viral in 2018 and has steadily become a bigger and bigger favorite. This briney pie is most often baked with garlic sauce, topped with mozzarella, and dipped in ranch.

Fun Fact: Legend has it that a mother-daughter duo invented this pizza after a visit to the Pickle Festival.

What’s Your Vote?

Oh, So You Think Pizza Forecasting Is Easy?!

Pineapple pizza orders rose 76% in ’21, so we predicted the trend would continue into ’22. And…

6.1% fewer pineapple orders ’22

Its reign is over, but the war pineapple started will go on forever. Ashes to ashes, crust to crust.

As much as we love pizza, we love the people who make it even more. Slice exists to support all the indie pizzerias that make our neighborhoods stronger.

People want deliciously fresh pizza, not processed, predictable pies. There are more indie pizzerias in America than any brand of corporate pizza.

Indie pizzerias don’t just make pies — they create jobs for the community. When you eat local pizza, you support the 213,898 people employed by neighborhood shops.

We believe local pizzerias deserve all the advantages of big chains without compromising their independence. That’s what fuels our mission to keep local thriving. Through specialized tech, data insights, targeted marketing, and collective buying power, we empower pizzerias to better serve digitally-minded customers and build thriving local businesses.

Ilir Sela started Slice in 2015 to modernize his friends’ and family’s New York City pizzerias. Today, we partner with restaurants in over 3,000 cities and all 50 states, forming the nation’s largest community of independent pizzerias. Learn more about Slice.
